title: Allow start/stop aria2 Service from outher apps
message:
Allow start/stop aria2 Service from outher apps

This commit adds a public BroadcastReceiver, which acts as intermediary
between outside Intents and the foreground Service (so the Service itself
does not have to be exported). Three commands are currently supported:

* net.sf.aria2.service.START_SERVICE
* net.sf.aria2.service.STOP_SERVICE
* net.sf.aria2.service.RESTART_SERVICE

The receiver does not have intent filters, the broadcast must specifically
target it.

title: Allow to configure the network, used by aria2
message:
Allow to configure the network, used by aria2

There are 3 options:

1. Do not do anything special (e.g. keep the old behavior of
letting bionic do the network choice)
2. Use interface specified by name, IP or hostname
3. Use the interface, correpsonding to Android Network of choice as
reported by ConnectivityManager

In 2nd and 3rd cases the frontend will attempt to resolve interface name
to IP address (because bionic apparently isn't able to do that for us).

title: Improve error reporting code
message:
Improve error reporting code

At some point it was broken and started to sporadically show incomplete
line fragments (possibly empty). Now it should correctly pick up to 200
characters at the start and equal amount at the end for displaying to user.
